- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of topic models for text analysis and its evolution in the field of social science. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of topic models for exploring large collections of unstructured text in social science research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as topic models are a family of statistical-based algorithms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses methods for evaluation and interpretation of topic models. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of topic models in social science research.
